## Distance Correlation and the Illusion of Standard Deviation

This article, or rather, the concept it points to, concerns the rather mundane notion of [distance correlation](/Distance_correlation), specifically its relationship to [distance standard deviation](/Distance_standard_deviation). It’s a redirect, a signpost pointing away from a less specific topic towards a more granular aspect of statistical analysis. Frankly, the idea of an entire article dedicated to a redirect is almost as amusing as the inherent limitations of relying solely on standard deviation when the underlying data is anything but standard.

